<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/44601AVBDVLNHRGJHQBVDLKSCHSSDGBJK>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Improv 103: Short Form Scenes!";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Improv 103</h1><h2>Short Form Scenes!</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Day & Time:</span> Select Saturdays & Sundays at<span><br/></span>11:00am – 3:00pm (8 hours)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Age:</span> 19+<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Level Required: </span>Improv 102<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Cost:</span> $195<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Continue your improv education with short form games and scenes, incorporating the lessons and takeaways from Improv 101/102. We will build on the ability to “make a scene matter” as well as explore simple game handles that can add fun twists to regular scenes!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>REFUND POLICY:<span><br/></span>No refunds. Day one and two of training must be attended consecutively in the booked weekend to ensure a trusting and collaborative experience for all students. Completion of course and eligibility for class advancement requires full attendance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>LOCK OUT POLICY:<span><br/></span>Doors will lock 15 minutes after the class begins. Late comers will not be permitted.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>WAITLIST:<span><br/></span>If a class is sold out for a date you're hoping to attend, you can write in to <span class=\"BoldText\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca\">boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca</a></span> to be added to a waitlist. While TIC can't guarantee you'll get a spot, we'll reach out if we can fit you in the class.
""";
