<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/45601AKQVBSQHJBQRVBTCHVPGDDNQTRGL>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Improv 201: Mastering The Mid-Form!";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Improv 201</h1><h2>Mastering The Mid-Form!</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Day & Time:</span> Saturdays & Sundays at 11:00am – 3:00pm (8 hours)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Age: </span>19+<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Level Required:</span> Improv 103<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Cost: </span>$195<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>If you’ve seen one of our weekday shows, you’ve already met mid-form: 15–20 minute improv montages packed with big laughs and smart connections. In this 8-hour course, you’ll learn how we approach mid-form improv by exploring edits, callbacks, and ensemble work, all while building a cohesive 15–20 minute set from only a few suggestions. Expect lots of time on your feet; it’s time to get those reps in and master the mid-form!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>REFUND POLICY:<span><br/></span>No refunds. Day one and two of training must be attended consecutively in the booked weekend to ensure a trusting and collaborative experience for all students. Completion of course and eligibility for class advancement requires full attendance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>LOCK OUT POLICY:<span><br/></span>Doors will lock 15 minutes after the class begins. Late comers will not be permitted.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>WAITLIST:<span><br/></span>If a class is sold out for a date you're hoping to attend, you can write in to <span class=\"BoldText\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca\">boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca</a></span> to be added to a waitlist. While TIC can't guarantee you'll get a spot, we'll reach out if we can fit you in the class.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-06-13T11:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/files/0bd021cc-8580-4ff6-9f09-5d794510397e.jpg>;
