<http://www.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/event/43601AMKQJGTDVBKLNSTTJVLMKDNDDDLS>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Task It! Space Object Improv with Mary Saunders";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Task It! Space Object Improv with Mary Saunders</h1><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Time: </span>3:30pm – 5:30pm<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Age: </span>19+<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Level Required: </span>Improv 102 or equivalent experience (email <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:education@theimprovcentre.ca\">education@theimprovcentre.ca</a> if you’re not sure).<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Workshop Capacity:</span> 14 people<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Cost: </span>$75<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This workshop explores the significance of tasking in scenes and how it can be used to communicate beyond words. Discuss and practice basic technique, commitment, and ultimately, how tasking comes together to diversify the visual and emotional landscape of your scenes, beyond dialogue alone!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>About the teacher:<span><br/></span>Mary (she/they) is a Vancouver-based comedian. Her initial improv training was with Instant Theatre and UBCimprov, then later Blind Tiger Comedy. Now she can be regularly found performing as a Mainstage ensemble member at The Improv Centre, a co-creator and producer of WikiProv, and a member of Grad School Improv. Mary is passionate about using her over 10 years experience as a foundation for teaching others the skills they need to begin and expand their own improv journeys. Mary is also a satirist, having published works via Reductress and the Beaverton, and a sketch comedian. Mary is stoked to be here and would do anything for you.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>REFUND POLICY:<span><br/></span>No refunds. Day one and two of training must be taken consecutively in the booked weekend to ensure a trusting and collaborative experience for all students. Completion of course and eligibility for class advancement requires full attendance.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>LOCK OUT POLICY:<span><br/></span>Doors will lock 15 minutes after the class begins. Late comers will not be permitted.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>WAITLIST:<span><br/></span>If a class is sold out for a date you're hoping to attend, you can write in to <span class=\"BoldText\"><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca\">boxoffice@theimprovcentre.ca</a></span> to be added to a waitlist. While TIC can't guarantee you'll get a spot, we'll reach out if we can fit you in the class.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-02T15:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/files/e75bf5b7-80d5-4ead-be88-8f45ca46ac85.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/location/603AMBLCJQMLRJDMDQKBNHDKQPPDPCQLJ>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/improvcentrevancouver/organization/the-improv-centre>;
  schema:url <https://theimprovcentre.ca/shows/>;
  schema:offers _:61bf61df540e4d49aa04255634b383c75465;
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-05-02T16:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

